decision_conditions: Application for approval of the reserved matters shall be made to the Local Planning Authority before the expiration of three years from the date of this outline permission.Reason:To comply with Section 92 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended by S.51 of the Planning and Compulsory Purchase Act  2004)

The development permitted shall be begun  before the expiration of two years from the date of approval of the last of the reserved matters to be approved. Reason:To comply with Section 92 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended by S.51 of the Planning and Compulsory Purchase Act  2004)

Approval of the details of the appearance, layout, scale, the means of access thereto and the landscaping of the site (hereinafter called "the reserved matters") shall be obtained from the Local Planning Authority, and the development shall not be carried out except in accordance with the details so approvedReason:The application is in outline only, and these details remain to be submitted and approved.

No external construction works, deliveries, external running of plant and equipment or internal works audible outside the site boundary shall take place on the site other than between the hours of 0800  to 1800 on Monday to Friday and 0800 to 1300 on Saturday or on Sundays, Public or Bank Holidays without the prior written permission of the Local Planning Authority.Reason:To ensure that the proposed construction work does not cause undue nuisance and disturbance to neighbouring properties at unreasonable hours and in accordance with Policy G.36 of the Unitary Development Plan.

The development shall not be commenced until a scheme specifying the provisions to be made to control noise emanating from the site during construction works has been submitted to, and approved by, the Local Planning Authority.  This scheme should include details of the construction methods to be employed, for example piling, the duration of such activities, the equipment to be used and the proposed hours of operation.  All construction activities associated with the development shall be carried out in accordance with the recommendations contained in British Standard 5228, Parts 1 and 2, 1984 and Part 4, 1986.Reason:To ensure that the proposed construction work does not cause nuisance and disturbance to neighbouring occupiers and in accordance with Policy G.36 of the Unitary Development Plan.

The development shall not be commenced until a scheme specifying the provisions to be made to control dust emanating from the site has been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority.Reason:To safeguard the amenity of neighbouring occupiers.

With the exception of the redevelopment of Hewetts Quay, those premises to be refurbished and those companies to be relocated, no commercial, industrial or residential building shall be occupied until alteration works to the access to the easterly end of the footbridge have been completed in accordance with details, including complete drawings, specifications, design and construction of the works, submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority in consultation with Transport for London.Reason:To ensure continued integrity of the Highbridge Road footbridge structure and to ensure continued safety of the traffic using the A406 which forms part of the Greater London Road Network (GLA).

A copy of the scheme safety audit for road, footbridge and any other works owned by or expected to be adopted by the local or highway authorities shall be prepared for approval by the Local Planning Authority in consultation with Transport for London prior to commencement of any of these works.Reason:To ensure continued integrity of the Highbridge Road footbridge structure and to ensure continued safety of the traffic using the A406 which forms part of the Greater London Road Network (GLA).

No part of the footbridge ramp structure shall be demolished or reconstructed prior to obtaining approval from the Local Planning Authority in consultation with Transport for London of the Approval in Principle (AIP) documents including the Design and Check Certificates.Reason:To ensure continued integrity of the Highbridge Road footbridge structure and to ensure continued safety of the traffic using the A406 which forms part of the Greater London Road Network (GLA).

No part of the footbridge ramp structure shall be placed in an adverse position such that it can be subjected to  vehicle impact loading by changes in road geometry without providing either a suitable and approved vehicle restraint system or, where this is impracticable, strengthening of the existing structure.Reason:To ensure continued integrity of the Highbridge Road footbridge structure and to ensure continued safety of the traffic using the A406 which forms part of the Greater London Road Network (GLA).

Access to all parts of the ramp structure for the purposes of inspection and maintenance shall be made available at all times.  A list of persons to be contacted in this regard is to be supplied to Transport for London Street Management at the outset and any subsequent changes in the persons to be contacted shall be notified to Transport for London Street Management.Reason:To ensure continued integrity of the Highbridge Road footbridge structure and to ensure continued safety of the traffic using the A406 which forms part of the Greater London Road Network (GLA).

No part of any building hereby approved shall be erected within 3 metres of the footbridge ramp structure.Reason:To ensure continued integrity of the Highbridge Road footbridge structure and to ensure continued safety of the traffic using the A406 which forms part of the Greater London Road Network (GLA).

No building hereby approved shall impose any additional loading on the foundations of the footbridge ramp structure or otherwise serve to undermine the structure.Reason:To ensure continued integrity of the Highbridge Road footbridge structure and to ensure continued safety of the traffic using the A406 which forms part of the Greater London Road Network (GLA).

No development shall take place which will reduce the ground cover to the foundations of the footbridge ramp structure to less than 0.6 metre.Reason:To ensure continued integrity of the Highbridge Road footbridge structure and to ensure continued safety of the traffic using the A406 which forms part of the Greater London Road Network (GLA).

No part of the footbridge ramp structure shall be demolished until a safe alternative route to the footbridge has been agreed with the Local Planning Authority in consultation with Transport for London. The footbridge shall be temporarily closed as necessary during the works in the interests of pedestrian safety.Reason:To ensure continued integrity of the Highbridge Road footbridge structure and to ensure continued safety of the traffic using the A406 which forms part of the Greater London Road Network (GLA).

No temporary or permanent fixing shall be attached to any part of the footbridge ramp structure.Reason:To ensure continued integrity of the Highbridge Road footbridge structure and to ensure continued safety of the traffic using the A406 which forms part of the Greater London Road Network (GLA).

No connections shall be made to the drainage system serving the footbridge structure and in the ownership of Transport for London.Reason:To ensure continued integrity of the Highbridge Road footbridge structure and to ensure continued safety of the traffic using the A406 which forms part of the Greater London Road Network (GLA).

The total floorspace of the retail unit hereby approved shall not be increased by internal alteration without the prior approval of the Local Planning Authority.Reason:To protect the vitality and viability of Barking and East Ham Town Centres

With the exception of the redevelopment of Hewetts Quay, those premises to be refurbished and those companies to be relocated, no commercial, industrial or residential building shall be occupied until off-site highway works to improve the access to the site have been completed in accordance with details submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority.Reason:To ensure that the proposed development does not prejudice the free flow of traffic or conditions of general safety along the adjoining highway.

No commercial or industrial building hereby permitted shall be occupied until a green travel plan has been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. The green travel plan should outline proposals to minimise car-borne trips and encourage the use of public transport and, once approved, should thereafter be maintained.Reason:To encourage the use of alternatives to the private car as a means of accessing the site in the interests of sustainability and minimising polluting emissions.

The retail unit(s) shall not commence trading until provision has been made within the site for bus stopping facilities in both directions and the construction of an appropriate dedicated bus route including the provision of satisfactory footway and kerb details. All such works shall be carried out in accordance with details to be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.Reason:To ensure the provision of bus facilities which are essential for public transport use of the scheme and the successful implementation of the green travel plan.

All parts of the development, including the car parks and all external circulation areas, shall be designed to be accessible to people with disabilities in accordance with details submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.Reason:In the interests of providing easier access within the development to people with disabilities.

The Class A3 uses hereby permitted shall not be commenced until details of the extract ventilation system and odour control equipment, including details of any external ducting and measures to control noise and vibration, have been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority and the equipment so approved has been installed. Such approved equipment shall thereafter be operated at all times when cooking is carried out and maintained in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.Reason:To safeguard the appearance of the development and minimise the impact of cooking smells and odours.

Before the development hereby approved is commenced a survey of existing noise levels, details of which shall be agreed with the Local Planning Authority, shall be carried out and, where necessary, based on the results of this survey, details of the methods to protect future residential occupiers from existing and proposed noise levels should be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority.Reason:In order to ascertain which Noise Exposure Category the site falls into and to safeguard the amenities of the future occupiers of the development.

No building hereby permitted shall be occupied until details of the means of accommodating either the relevant trade or household refuse have been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority.Reason:To provide satisfactory refuse storage provision in the interests of public health and to protect the appearance of the development.

No part of the development, with the exception of those companies to be relocated, shall be commenced until details of the boundary treatment have been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. In the case of relocated companies the boundary treatment for those individual sites shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority prior to the commencement of development. No part of the site shall be occupied until the approved boundary treatment for that part has been provided.Reason:To ensure the satisfactory means of enclosure for the proposed development in the interests of the visual amenity of the area.

No commercial, industrial or residential development shall commence until details for the parking of motor cycles and covered parking of cycles have been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority (including location and detailed design, method of securing cycles and numbers of motor cycles/cycles to be accommodated). No commercial, industrial or residential development shall be occupied until the motor cycle/cycle parking required to serve the building has been constructed. The approved parking shall thereafter be kept in an operational condition and shall not be used for any other purpose without the prior approval of the Local Planning Authority.Reason:In the interests of promoting alternative modes of travel other than the private car in order to minimise polluting emissions.

All commercial and industrial parts of the development shall make satisfactory provision for servicing. No commercial or industrial building shall be occupied until details of servicing have been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority and thereafter all service areas shall be retained for the loading, unloading and turning of vehicles servicing the scheme. All loading or unloading of goods from vehicles, other than private motor vehicles arriving at or departing from the premises, shall be carried out within such areas.Reason:In the interests of highway and pedestrian safety and the amenity of the area.

Goods and materials associated with the proposed retail and industrial unit(s) shall not be stored or sold in the open without the prior approval of the Local Planning Authority.Reason:To protect the appearance of the area.

No building hereby permitted shall be developed until details of external lighting to serve the building have been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. No building hereby permitted shall be occupied until the relevant external lighting has been installed.Reason:In the interests of highway safety and public amenity.

The existing ground levels adjacent to the river walls shall not be altered nor shall the river walls be subjected to any additional horizontal or vertical loading (other than to accommodate the construction of the riverside walk and that for which they were designed) either temporarily or permanently, without the prior written approval of the Local Planning Authority in consultation with the Environment Agency.Reason:To maintain the integrity of the flood defences.

The approved development shall make provision for a "buffer zone" 10 metres wide where possible alongside the River Roding/ Barking Creek and Hand Trough Creek, in accordance with details which shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The buffer zone will incorporate a riverside walk/cycleway together with soft and hard landscaping and associated street furniture and public art. The approved planting scheme shall incorporate native species of British origin.Reason:To expand and enhance the river corridor, provide undisturbed refuges for wildlife and in the interests of promoting public access to the riverside.

A landscape management plan, including long term design objectives, management responsibilities and maintenance schedules for all landscape areas, other than small, privately owned, domestic gardens, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority before the development commences. Unless otherwise agreed the landscape management plan shall be carried out as approved.Reason:To protect and enhance the river corridor.

There shall be no new hard bank installed along Barking Creek and Hand Trough Creek. However, for the avoidance of doubt, the existing hard bank shall be maintained and reinforced/refurbished where necessary.Reason:To protect the river corridor.

The construction of the surface water drainage system shall be carried out in accordance with details submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. No building hereby permitted shall be constructed until it has been demonstrated that the drainage system can accommodate the development.Reason:To prevent pollution of the water environment.

The construction of the sewerage infrastructure system to receive foul water discharges from the site shall be carried out in accordance with details submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. No building hereby approved shall be constructed until it has been demonstrated that the sewerage system can accommodate the development.Reason:To prevent the pollution of the water environment.

No building hereby permitted shall be constructed until details of the proposed foundations have been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority.Reason:To prevent pollution of the water environment.

The retail unit(s) shall only be used for the sale of home improvement and associated products, DIY goods, plumbing and hardware goods, timber and building products, paint and wallpaper, garden supplies, furniture, carpets and other floor coverings, soft furnishings, homewares, electrical goods, computers, office equipment and supplies, pets and pet products, motor accessories, cycles and cycle accessories and for no other purpose including those set out in Class A1 of the Schedule of the Town and Country Planning (Use Classes) Order 1987 without the prior approval of the Local Planning Authority.Reason:To protect the vitality and viabilty of Barking and East Ham Town Centres.

No commercial, industrial or residential development shall commence until details of a car parking scheme have been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. For clarification purposes this permission does not give consent to the number of car parking spaces shown on the illustrative plans submitted in support of the application. No commercial, industrial or residential building shall be occupied until the car parking required to serve the building has been constructed. The approved parking spaces shall thereafter be retained permanently for the accommodation of occupiers and visitors to the site and not for any other purpose unless alternative spaces are provided elsewhere on site.Reason:To ensure that adequate car parking accommodation is made permanently available in the interests of highway safety.

The retail unit(s) hereby approved shall not exceed the gross floorspace data given with the application (9,290 m2) and no other ancillary retail trading areas shall be provided without the prior approval of the Local Planning Authority.Reason:To protect the vitality and viability of Barking and East Ham Town Centres.

No commercial, industrial or residential development shall commence until a detailed design for the riverside walk/cycleway has been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. No commercial, industrial or residential development shall be occupied until the riverside walk/cycleway for that part has been constructed.Reason:In the interests of promoting public access to the riverside in accordance with U.D.P. policy E12.

The development of the site shall be in general conformity with the arrangement of uses shown in the indicative zonal masterplan shown on drawing number 98130 dated April 2000.Reason:To provide greater certainty of the site layout in the interests of the proper planning of the area.

The development shall not be commenced until a survey of land contamination has been carried out on the site to the approval of the Local Planning Authority and any work shown by the survey to be necessary shall be carried out in accordance with the requirements of the Local Planning Authority.Reason	To protect excavation workers from subsoil hazards, the amenities of the locality and in order to quantify any hazards already existing on the site in accordance with Policy G28 of the Unitary Development Plan.
